### LAYER 1: BPS Sakernas \'97 The Statistical Foundation\
\
**What it provides:**\
- Average net wage/salary per month by: Province \'d7 Main Job Type (KBJI 4-digit occupation code)\
- Dimensions available: Province (34), Education level, Age group, Industry (KBLI), Urban/Rural\
- Updated: Semi-annually (February and August survey rounds), published with ~6-month lag\
- Latest available: August 2025 data published December 2025\
- URL: bps.go.id/en/statistics-table (publicly accessible, downloadable)\
\
**What it does NOT provide:**\
- Specific job titles (Software Engineer, Product Manager) \'97 only 4-digit KBJI occupation codes like "2512 \'97 Software Developer" or "1211 \'97 Director of Administration"\
- City-level data (only province-level)\
- Experience-band breakdowns\
- Company-type breakdowns (startup vs MNC)\
\
**How to use it (the derivation chain):**\
1. Download Sakernas wage table by Province \'d7 KBJI occupation code\
2. Map common job titles to their nearest KBJI code (e.g., "Software Engineer" \uc0\u8594  KBJI 2512)\
3. Apply urban multiplier for city estimation (Jakarta = 1.35\'961.45x province average based on BPS urban/rural differential)\
4. Apply education band adjustment (S1 = 1.0x, S2 = 1.3\'961.5x based on BPS education wage table)\
5. Apply industry sector multiplier (Tech sector = 1.4\'961.6x national average for equivalent occupation)\
\
**Honest confidence level:** P50 salary derived this way will be within \'b120% of actual market for most job categories. NOT precise. Good enough for "Wajar / Tidak Wajar" verdict logic, but NOT good enough for P25/P75 detail.\
\
**Legal status:** BPS explicitly licenses public data for reuse with attribution under the BPS data policy (Peraturan BPS No. 4/2018). Commercial use with attribution is permitted. The World Bank, ILO, and JICA all commercially reference BPS Sakernas in paid reports. Risk rating: LOW.\
